Shell ' s Wavin ups stake in Polish plant . Plastics maker Wavin BV , 50 - percent owned unit of Royal Dutch / Shell , has raised to 67 percent its stake in its Polish subsidiary Wavin - Metalplast , PAP news agency said on Monday . It said Wavin ' s equity in Wavin - Metalplast , a plastic installation materials maker based western Poland , has been increased through a purchase of a 26 - percent stake from the treasury . " We want to invest in new products and expand the existing production on the Polish market , " PAP quoted Wavin president Fons Driessen as saying . Wavin - Metalplast employs 450 workers and specialises in plastic pipes production . PAP report gave no further details . - - Warsaw Newsroom + 48 22 653 9700 
